-> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) * np.exp(item - bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) * np.exp(item - bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    ratio = item / bins\n    return np.cos(np.pi * ratio) * np.log(item)\n```\n\n### Implementation 3:\nThis implementation uses the absolute difference between the item and each bin, then applies the square root of that difference.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.sqrt(np.abs(item - bins))\n```\n\n### Implementation 4:\nThis implementation calculates the remaining space in each bin after placing the item and uses the exponential of that remaining space.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins - item\n    return np.exp(remaining)\n```\n\n### Implementation 5:\nThis implementation uses the item size to calculate the ratio with each bin and then applies the sine function to that ratio, multiplied by the item size.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    ratio = item / bins\n    return item * np.sin(np.pi * ratio)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.sqrt(item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.std(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) \n', 'def priority(item: float, 