but some of these might not be valid or could cause issues like division by zero. I should add a small epsilon to avoid that.\n\nLet me adjust the functions to include 1e-10 where necessary.\n\nFunction 1:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * np.sin(bins / item)\n\nBut wait, what if item is zero? We should add a small epsilon to avoid division by zero.\n\nSo, modify to:\n\nreturn np.exp(item) * np.sin(bins / (item + 1e-10))\n\nBut wait, item is a float, so adding 1e-10 is okay.\n\nFunction 2:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(bins + 1e-10) * np.cos(item)\n\nFunction 3:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.tan(bins) * np.sqrt(item + 1e-10)\n\nFunction 4:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    max_bin = np.max(bins)\n    return np.arcsin(bins / (max_bin + 1e-10)) * item\n\nFunction 5:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log10(bins + 1e-10) ** item\n\nFunction 6:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    mean_bins = np.mean(bins)\n    return np.abs(bins - mean_bins) * item\n\nFunction 7:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.sin(bins) * np.log(item + 1e-10)\n\nFunction 8:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    max_bin = np.max(bins)\n    return np.cos(bins / (max_bin + 1e-10)) * item\n\nFunction 9:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    min_bin = np.min(bins)\n    return np.tan(bins / (min_bin + 1e-10)) * item\n\nFunction 10:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * np.log2(bins + 1e-10)\n\nWait, but in Function 10, if bins are zero, adding 1e-10 is necessary to avoid log of zero.\n\nYes, that's handled.\n\nNow, let me check each function to ensure they are unique in their combination of operations.\n\nFunction 1 uses e