ty\n\n loss = 4.76119179517893\n\n### Example of a Combined Heuristic:\ndef priority(item: np.ndarray, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Heuristic: Best Fit Decreasing with Most Empty\n    # Sort bins by size and item by size\n    # Then, for each bin, compute how well it fits the item\n    # Best fit: bin with the smallest remaining space that can fit the item\n    # Decreasing: sort bins from largest to smallest\n    # Most Empty: prefer bins with more empty space\n    # Combine best fit with most empty\n    # Compute fit score\n    fit_score = np.exp(item / (bins + 1e-8))\n    # Sort bins by fit score\n    sorted_bins = np.argsort(-fit_score)\n    # Compute most empty score\n    most_empty_score = np.std(bins)\n    # Combine fit_score and most_empty_score\n    priority = fit_score * most_empty_score\n    return priority\n\n loss = 5.4648899535867\n\n### Example of a Combined Heuristic with Multiple Operations:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Heuristic: Best Fit with Most Empty\n    # Compute fit score for each bin\n    fit_score = np.exp(item / (bins + 1e-8))\n    # Compute most empty score\n    most_empty_score = np.std(bins)\n    # Combine fit_score and most_empty_score\n    priority = fit_score * most_empty_score\n    return priority\n\n loss = 5.4648899535867\n\n### Example of a Combined Heuristic with Multiple Operations:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Heuristic: Best Fit with Most Empty\n    # Compute fit score for each bin\n    fit_score = np.exp(item / (bins + 1e-8))\n    # Compute most empty score\n    most_empty_score = np.std(bins)\n    # Combine fit_score and most_empty_score\n    priority = fit_score * most_empty_score\n    return priority\n\n loss = 5.4648899535867\n\n### Example of a Combined Heuristic with Multiple Operations:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Heuristic: Best Fit with Most Empty\n    # Compute fit score for each bin\n    f