on 3:\n- Term1: np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins)) * np.sqrt(bins)\n- Term2: np.exp(item - np.max(bins))\n- Combine them.\n\nFunction 4:\n- Term1: np.log(item + 1) * np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins))\n- Term2: np.mean(bins) * np.exp(item - bins)\n- Combine them.\n\nWait, but I need to ensure each function is unique. Maybe vary the aggregating functions and the trigonometric functions used.\n\nLet me try to create each function step by step, ensuring each has a unique combination.\n\nFunction 1:\nUse np.mean(bins), multiply by item, then add an exponential term based on item and bins.\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) + np.exp(item - bins)\n", 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 5 + np.log(item + 3)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 6 + np.sqrt(item / bins) * 5\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item * np.mean(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * item) * np.mean(bins) + np.cos(np.pi * bins) * 5\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 7 + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 3\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.mean(bins) * np.exp(item) + np.sqrt(item / np.mean(bins)) * 6 + np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 4\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) 